      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. So if the percale is more like a \"wall\" of threads, would the density prevent the fabric from being easily compromised by external elements? Like, if the weave is tight enough, can we be sure that nothing—not even tiny particles or loose fibers—could seep through the weave itself?",
